<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2017-10-19</DATELINE><TITLE>Association of visitation policy and health care-acquired respiratory viral infections in hospitalized children</TITLE><BODY>Visitor restriction policies are meant to prevent health care-acquired viral infections; however, data on their efficacy in hospitalized children are limited. We report a 37% reduction in health care-acquired respiratory viral infections in a children's hospital following standardization of the visitation policy that limited the number of visitors during a patient's hospitalization.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>